  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="Poem23"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="other"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="society"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
          <l>My neighbor’s daughter has created a city</l>
          <l>you cannot see</l> 
          <l>on an island to which you cannot swim</l>
          <l>Gentle thou art and therefore to be won,</l>
          <l>ruled by a noble princess and her athletic consort</l>
          <l>all the buildings are glass so that lies are impossible</l>
          <l>beneath the city they have buried certain words</l>
          <l>which can never be spoken again</l>
          <l>chiefly the word divorce which is eaten by maggots</l>
          <l>when it rains you hear chimes</l>
          <l>rabbits race through its suburbs</l>
          <l>the name of the city is one you can almost pronounce</l>
          
                 
